{"title_page": "Caproni Ca.308 Borea", "text_new": "{{About|the Ca.308 ''Borea'' airliner|the Ca.308 ground-attack aircraft|Caproni A.P.1}}\n<!-- This article is a part of [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Aircraft]]. Please see [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Aircraft/page content]] for recommended layout. -->\n{|{{Infobox Aircraft Begin\n |name=Ca.308 Borea\n |image=Caproni Ca.308.jpg\n |caption=\n}}{{Infobox Aircraft Type\n |type=Airliner\n |manufacturer=[[Caproni]]\n |designer=\n |first flight=[[1935 in aviation|1935]]\n |introduced=\n |retired=\n |status=\n |primary user=[[Ala Littoria]]\n |more users=\n |produced=\n |number built=8\n |variants with their own articles=\n}}\n|}\n\nThe '''Caproni Ca.308 ''Borea''''' (\"North Wind\") was a small [[airliner]] built in [[Italy]] in the mid-1930s.\n\n==Development==\nThe Ca.308 was a streamlined, low-wing [[Cantilever#Aircraft|cantilevered]] [[monoplane]] design of conventional configuration. Its [[Landing gear|undercarriage]] was not retractable. The [[Conventional landing gear|mainwheel]]s were fitted with [[Aircraft fairing|spat]]s.\n\nThe prototype, designated '''Ca.306''', was exhibited at the [[Milan Exhibition]] of 1935.\n\nThe basic design of the Ca.308 subsequently served as the basis for a large family of military aircraft, beginning with the [[Caproni Ca.309]].\n\n==Operational history==\nThe Italian airline ''[[Ala Littoria]]'' ordered five examples.\n\nThe Italian government ordered two aircraft for general-purpose use by its colonial administration in [[Libya]].\n\nAll these aircraft received the '''Ca.308''' designation.\n\n==Variants==\n;Ca 306:The prototype, exhibited at the [[Milan Exhibition]] of 1935.\n;Ca 308 ''Borea'':Production aircraft, Seven built.\n\n==Operators==\n;{{flag|Kingdom of Italy}}\n* ''[[Ala Littoria]]''<ref name=\"strp411\"/>\n* [[Regia Aeronautica]]\n;{{ITA}}\n*''[[Aeronautica Militare Italiana]]''<ref>[http://www.aeroflight.co.uk/waf/italy/af/ital-af2-all-time.htm aeroflight]</ref>\n\n<!-- ==Units using this aircraft/Operators (choose)== -->\n\n==Specifications (Ca.308)==\n[[File:Caproni Ca. 308 Borea, skica (Letectv\u00ed, November 1935).jpg|thumb|Caproni Ca. 308 Borea (Letectv\u00ed, November 1935)]]  \n{{Aircraft specs\n|ref=European Transport Aircraft since 1910<ref name=\"strp411\">{{Harvnb|Stroud|1966|p=411}}</ref>\n|prime units?=met\n<!--\n  \nGeneral characteristics\n-->\n|genhide= \n\n|crew=3\n|capacity=7 passengers\n|length m=12.87\n|length ft=\n|length in=\n|span m=16.20\n|span ft=\n|span in=\n|height m=\n|height ft=10\n|height in=8\n|height note=<ref name=\"thomp106\">{{Harvnb|Thompson|1963|p=106}}</ref>\n|wing area sqm=38.4\n|wing area sqft=\n|empty weight kg=1700\n|empty weight lb=\n|gross weight kg=2600\u20132700\n|gross weight lb=\n|fuel capacity=\n<!--\n        Powerplant\n-->\n|eng1 number=2\n|eng1 name=[[de Havilland Gipsy Six]] \n|eng1 type=six-cylinder [[inline engine (aviation)|inline engine]]\n|eng1 kw=<!-- prop engines -->\n|eng1 hp=200<!-- prop engines -->\n\n|prop blade number=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop name=\n|prop dia m=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop dia ft=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop dia in=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n\n<!--\n        Performance\n-->\n|perfhide=\n\n|max speed kmh=246\n|max speed mph=\n|max speed kts=\n|max speed mach=<!-- supersonic aircraft -->\n|cruise speed kmh=<!-- if max speed unknown -->\n|cruise speed mph=210<!-- if max speed unknown -->\n|cruise speed kts=\n|range km=1200\n|range miles=\n|range nmi=\n|ceiling m=5000\n|ceiling ft=\n|climb rate ms=\n|climb rate ftmin=846\n|climb rate note=<ref name=\"thomp106\"/>\n|more performance=\n\n|avionics=\n}}\n\n==See also==\n{{aircontent\n<!-- include as many lines are appropriate. additional lines/entries with carriage return. -->\n|related=<!-- related developments -->\n|similar aircraft=<!-- similar or comparable aircraft -->\n|lists=<!-- related lists -->\n|see also=<!-- other relevant information -->\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Caproni Ca.308 Borea}}\n{{reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |last=Stroud |first=John |title=European Transport Aircraft since 1910 |year=1966 |location=London |publisher=Putnam |oclc=895249324 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last= Taylor |first= Michael J. H. |title=Jane's Encyclopedia of Aviation |year=1989 |publisher=Studio Editions |location=London |pages=236 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Thompson |first=Jonathon |title=Italian Civil and Military Aircraft 1930\u20131945 |year=1963 |location= |publisher=Aero Publishers, Inc. |isbn=0-8168-6500-0 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |title=World Aircraft Information Files |publisher=Bright Star Publishing|location=London |pages=File 891 Sheet 11 }}\n* [http://www.airwar.ru/enc/cw1/ca308.html \u0423\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u043a \u043d\u0435\u0431\u0430]\n{{refend}}\n\n{{Caproni aircraft}}\n\n[[Category:Caproni aircraft|Ca.308]]\n[[Category:1930s Italian airliners]]\n[[Category:Low-wing aircraft]]\n[[Category:Aircraft first flown in 1935]]\n[[Category:Twin piston-engined tractor aircraft]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the Ca.308 ''Borea'' airliner|the Ca.308 ground-attack aircraft|Caproni A.P.1}}\n<!-- This article is a part of [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Aircraft]]. Please see [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Aircraft/page content]] for recommended layout. -->\n{|{{Infobox Aircraft Begin\n |name=Ca.308 Borea\n |image=Caproni Ca.308.jpg\n |caption=\n}}{{Infobox Aircraft Type\n |type=Airliner\n |manufacturer=[[Caproni]]\n |designer=\n |first flight=[[1935 in aviation|1935]]\n |introduced=\n |retired=\n |status=\n |primary user=[[Ala Littoria]]\n |more users=\n |produced=\n |number built=8\n |variants with their own articles=\n}}\n|}\n\nThe '''Caproni Ca.308 ''Borea''''' (\"North Wind\") was a small [[airliner]] built in [[Italy]] in the mid-1930s.\n\n==Development==\nThe Ca.308 was a streamlined, low-wing [[Cantilever#Aircraft|cantilevered]] [[monoplane]] design of conventional configuration. Its [[Landing gear|undercarriage]] was not retractable. The [[Conventional landing gear|mainwheel]]s were fitted with [[Aircraft fairing|spat]]s.\n\nThe prototype, designated '''Ca.306''', was exhibited at the [[Milan Exhibition]] of 1935.\n\nThe basic design of the Ca.308 subsequently served as the basis for a large family of military aircraft, beginning with the [[Caproni Ca.309]].\n\n==Operational history==\nThe Italian airline ''[[Ala Littoria]]'' ordered five examples.\n\nThe Italian government ordered two aircraft for general-purpose use by its colonial administration in [[Libya]].\n\nAll these aircraft received the '''Ca.308''' designation.\n\n==Variants==\n;Ca 306:The prototype, exhibited at the [[Milan Exhibition]] of 1935.\n;Ca 308 ''Borea'':Production aircraft, Seven built.\n\n==Operators==\n;{{flag|Kingdom of Italy}}\n* ''[[Ala Littoria]]''<ref name=\"strp411\"/>\n* [[Regia Aeronautica]]\n;{{ITA}}\n*''[[Aeronautica Militare Italiana]]''<ref>[http://www.aeroflight.co.uk/waf/italy/af/ital-af2-all-time.htm aeroflight]</ref>\n\n<!-- ==Units using this aircraft/Operators (choose)== -->\n\n==Specifications (Ca.308)==\n{{Aircraft specs\n|ref=European Transport Aircraft since 1910<ref name=\"strp411\">{{Harvnb|Stroud|1966|p=411}}</ref>\n|prime units?=met\n<!--\n        General characteristics\n-->\n|genhide= \n\n|crew=3\n|capacity=7 passengers\n|length m=12.87\n|length ft=\n|length in=\n|span m=16.20\n|span ft=\n|span in=\n|height m=\n|height ft=10\n|height in=8\n|height note=<ref name=\"thomp106\">{{Harvnb|Thompson|1963|p=106}}</ref>\n|wing area sqm=38.4\n|wing area sqft=\n|empty weight kg=1700\n|empty weight lb=\n|gross weight kg=2600\u20132700\n|gross weight lb=\n|fuel capacity=\n<!--\n        Powerplant\n-->\n|eng1 number=2\n|eng1 name=[[de Havilland Gipsy Six]] \n|eng1 type=six-cylinder [[inline engine (aviation)|inline engine]]\n|eng1 kw=<!-- prop engines -->\n|eng1 hp=200<!-- prop engines -->\n\n|prop blade number=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop name=\n|prop dia m=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop dia f